args:
The prosecutor has one final dirty trick, but
Jupiter still manages to stop him. After the
retrial, a freed Eryn thanks Jupiter before he
happily makes his way back to the Halidom.
Yo, yo, girl! Don't be a churl!\nGimme that key or I'm gonna make ya hurl!
Noooo! Give it back, you scuzz!

Hey, Mr. Prince! Try not to wince!
I'm gonna take some blood,
'cause we couldn't...uh...
talk you into it earlier!
Wait, is he on the ceiling—OW!
Excellent work, men. And now that I have\nthe blood and key, it's time to dispose of\nyou pathetic rabble. But first...
O sacred key! Do my bidding and fling\nopen the chest!
Yeeees... YEEEEES! Finally, the sacred relic\nwithin will be mine, with all the power\nand prosperity it brings!
There's something rising from the chest!\nIt looks like a goblet, but I'm guessing\nit's some sort of magical implement!
It started glowing when the Prince's\nblood touched it! Oh, this is baaaad!
This illustrious power is now mine.\nNow bow, you wretches! Bow before\nthe might of the Founder King!
That thing's nothing but a hunk\nof chunky crunky junk! What bunk!
No! It was shining! You all saw it!\nIt can't possibly be a fake!
Are you really going to start doubting it\nnow after all you've been through?

You lie and you cheat and you steal,
but the moment things don't go exactly
how you want, you give up? Pathetic!
Ha ha ha ha ha!

Okay, okay. Since I'm such a nice guy,
I'll let you in on the joke. The treasure is
real, and the thing inside it actually IS one
of Alberius' sacred relics.
And here's how I know: Alberius gifted it\nto me, and I then gave it to the old mayor\nof this town as proof of our friendship.
You received this from King Alberius?\nImpossible! And besides, if it IS real,\nwhy is it not working?!
Oh, it's working just fine—the dragonblood\nsaw to that. But it doesn't actually give\nany power to humans.
Then what the hell does it DO?!
It's a magical tool that summons me,\nthe Lightwyrm Jupiter, and enhances me\nwith dragonblood!
And hooo boy! That baby gave me so\nmuch mana that I am STUFFED!
No! This absolutely can't be happening!
Oh, but I just love that kind of reaction!\nAlso, I think you know what's coming next,\nso I sure hope you're ready!
Go, my imperial soldiers! Kill this thing!\nThrow your lives away for mine if that's\nwhat it takes!
Using us as shields? That ain't boss!\nYou think you are the best,\nbut you're actually weak sauce!
Ha ha ha! You think a few meatsacks can\nstop my lightning? Oh, but I can't wait to\nsee how all of your faces light up!
GWAAAAAAUUUGH! You...little...\nThere's no way...a dragon... is in this\ncourt of law... It's all...a bad dream...
Sorry there, boss, but this ain't no dream.\nPlus you'll need to pay us double,\n'cause we're tired of your scheme!
We've done it! We've finally done it!\nRope up the lot of these fools, boys!
Well, I'd say that wraps things up in a neat\nlittle package. Er, but Your Honor?
Seeing as we've lost the prosecutor,\nI assume we can reconvene at a later\ndate with a new one, yes?
Your request for a retrial is granted.\nFor now, court is adjourned.
A Few Days Later\nLittleton Court Waiting Room
I'm free! I'm free, I'm free, I'm freeeee!
Yep! It seems Jupiter was right on the\nmoney about what really happened.
The imperials all sang like canaries once\nthey lost their oh-so-generous patron.\nEasiest trial ever!
They didn't waste any time\nsetting me free either.
You really did it, Jupiter. Congratulations!
I'm sorry I doubted you, Jupiter.\nYou're the best lawyer in the world!
Yesss! Keep it coming! I love when people\ngive me the praise I so richly deserve!
Now I wish I hadn't said anything...\nAlso, things are all weird now.
Well, you knew the relic wasn't a\nbig deal, right?
So it shouldn't have mattered to you if the\njerk tried to open the chest. You could've\njust taken the prince and left town.
I don't understand why you went\nout of your way to represent me.
I have two reasons, actually, and the first\nis because I promised I would do so.

Indeed! Remember that ancestor we
discussed earlier? Well, I promised him
I'd come help if anything terrible ever
happened to his descendants.
When your ancestor was building this\ntown, I helped him bring prosperity to it\nin all sorts of ways.

And when I left, I gave him that magical
relic as a parting gift and told him that if
his descendants ever called me for help,
I'd be there.

That little beauty's main purpose is to call
me, you know? The dragonblood thing is
just a bonus. Don't know why people kept
going on about that part...
Having a dragon drop what they're doing to\ncome help should be enough of a treasure\nfor most people.
But I suppose the actual meaning got\ntwisted over the years and people started\nsaying it granted power and prosperity.
Okay, that all makes sense in terms of\nwhy you wanted to help me...
But you said you had another reason,\nright? So what was that?
Because I took quite the shine to you!\nWhy else would I have done it?

I'm actually a pretty fickle dragon, and if
my old friend's descendant had ended up
being as nasty as Gauron, I wouldn't have
bothered no matter what promises I made.
But lucky you, Eryn! You're the reason I\nwas able to stay true to my word!
Oh! Well, um...thank you. That makes me\nreally happy—and I'm absolutely going to\nfind a way to repay you for your trust!
I'll do everything I can to bring this town\nback to its former glory, and I'll work at\nit every day just to show you I'm serious!
Oh, right. With the current mayor cooling\nhis heels in the clink, you'll be the next\nmayor, as I recall?
And once we're back to our former glory,\nI'll find a way to thank you properly—so\nmake sure to come back here, all right?
I'm even willing to change the name of\nour town to Jupiterton. Whaddya think?\nPretty sweet name, eh?
Oh, that's not necessary, but thank you.\nI already have all the reward I need.
Of course! I got to see a conceited jerk\nhave his pride crushed before his eyes!
It's not every day you get to see someone\nplayed like a fiddle so perfectly, and I had\njust the most wonderful time! Ha ha ha!
(Yeesh. This dragon really does have a\nnasty side to his personality...)

Hey, Your Highness? Is the uh...great and
powerful friend my family spoke of always
like this? He seems more twisted and
flippant than I expected, ya know?
For the most part, yes—but he always\ntakes things seriously when it matters.
That's why I knew he wasn't joking when\nhe said he liked you. Right, Jupiter?
You know it! In fact, I like you so much\nthat I might even form a relationship with\nyou like I had with your ancestor.
Guess that makes us friends now.
So long as you keep me entertained!\nOh, and in the meantime, I'll allow you to\nhave Alberius's sacred treasure back.
Consider it proof of our friendship.\nAnd if you ever need help, you know\nwhat to do.
You know you can count on the world's\nhandsomest dragon being there for you!
Thank you, Jupiter! You're the best friend a\nfamily could ask for, and one heckuva\nlawyer to boot!
